Isolation ensures concurrent transactions behave like serial transactions.

4. Durability

Definition:
Once a transaction is COMMITTED, the changes become permanent.

Even if power fails immediately after commit, data should not be lost.

Key Points:
-> Happens after COMMIT.
-> Data is permanently stored.
-> Survives system crash.
-> Usually achieved using logs and disk storage.

Example

Before

A = ₹2000
B = ₹3000

After Commit

A = ₹1000
B = ₹4000

Even after restarting the database,

Values remain

A = ₹1000
B = ₹4000

Real-Life Example:

Online payment shows:

Payment Successful

Even if phone battery dies immediately,

Payment record still exists because it has been permanently committed.


Durability guarantees committed data is never lost.
